            "title": "Bursa Malaysia Closes Lower As FBM KLCI Dips 13.27 Points",
            "description": "<div class=\"tdb-block-inner td-fix-index\">\n<p>Bursa Malaysia ended Wednesday’s trading session on a softer note, with the FBM KLCI closing at 1,699.06 points, down 13.27 points or 0.77%. \n\n\n\n</p><p>Broader market indices also fell, with the FBM70 down 124.93 points (-0.71%), F4GBM slipping 8.35 points (-0.82%), and FBMEMAS retreating 96.34 points (-0.76%).</p><div class=\"g g-1\"><div class=\"g-dyn a-70 c-1\"></div></div>\n<p>Market activity was led by high-volume counters including SBS, ZETRIX, and IJM. \n\n\n\n</p><p>SBS fell 1 sen to 24 sen, with 76.2 million shares changing hands, while ZETRIX held steady at 80.5 sen with 69.9 million shares traded. \n\n\n\n</p><p>IJM declined 8 sen to RM2.57 on 67.5 million shares. \n\n\n\n</p><p>On the gainers’ side, SMRT rose 0.5 sen to 19 sen and CAPITALA added 2 sen to 52.5 sen.\n\n\n\n</p><p>Overall, investors remained cautious amid mixed regional cues and profit-taking in selected heavyweight counters, contributing to the broad-based declines across the local bourse.\n\n</p></div>",
